    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so if the structure is as fundamentally flawed as those critics say, then isn't the argument for its continued relevance kind of just an excuse to keep the current power balance in place? like, if the UN can't actually stop the big players from doing whatever they want, isn't it basically just a tool for legitimizing the status quo rather than an actual peacekeeping body?",
